                "name": "Joel Mikkelsen",
                "href": "/profile/Joel-Mikkelsen-1"
            },
            "answer_text": "Focus on the neck. The neck is the main \u2018interface\u2019 between your hands and the guitar, so if the neck is not right for you, you probably won\u2019t be happy with the guitar in the long run. The neck should be straight (i.e, not warped) and feel comfortable in your hand (i.e., comfortable width, thickness, and finish). Run your hands along the side of the neck; the frets should not stick out or feel sharp. Finally, play every single note on the guitar and listen for correct intonation and notes that ring out without buzzing or rattling. ",
